{"about_the_game":"<strong>A first-person perspective mystery puzzle-solving game.</strong><br><br>In the 1990s, a young Chinese individual established a website called Abnormal1999 in the United States, which collected a large amount of abnormal cases and events. Meanwhile, in China, a police officer named &quot;Liu Qingchun&quot; also founded the 403 Intelligence Division, which similarly gathered abnormal intelligence. Over the course of more than a decade, these two organizations gradually grew in size and began to oppose each other, employing numerous intelligence personnel to gather information and leads.<br><br>This game is the first installment of this series, with plans to release 2 episodes each month, totaling 6 episodes for a season. Each episode is both independent and interconnected. In this installment, a highly bizarre case is featured: <br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2817190/extras/Video3.gif?t=1739855023\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Season 1, Episode 1\u300aWith in the Obscurity\u300b</h2>the police discovered 7 bodies in a desolate forest, each belonging to a member of a local spiritual group participating in a &quot;spiritual practice.&quot; According to forensic analysis, all 7 individuals had no external injuries or signs of poisoning. At the time, there were a total of 8 participants in the spiritual practice, with one person missing. Interestingly, all the relatives of the deceased chose not to pursue the killer, leaving the case unsolved.<br><br>Players take on the role of one of the 8 individuals involved, gradually uncovering the truth of the events as an eyewitness to the &quot;spiritual practice&quot; incident.<br><br>Players must solve various puzzles and deduce the truth based on the &quot;clues&quot; obtained in the game.<br><br>You need to carefully read the clues you receive and play the game according to the clues provided.","background":"https://shared.akamai.steam